stylometry: @ Risk allows you to run several simulations at one time by determining the optimal solution for the input cells.  By running multiple simulations, you are finding the best possible solution to the problem.  Each input has multiple iterations that it tries in order to find that solution.  When a simulation is run with 5 inputs, it runs a preset amount of iterations per input.  For example, when you run 1000 iterations, it is doing that for each of the 5 inputs.  This information gives you the average of the 5000 iterations, which is extremely accurate.
